Description: Implements Bootstrap-Aggregated Penalized Meta-Regression (BAP-MR)
    for small-sample evidence synthesis. Standard regularization methods (LASSO,
    Ridge) can paradoxically increase overfitting in meta-regression when the
    number of studies is small relative to the number of moderators. BAP-MR
    resolves this by averaging penalized coefficients across bootstrap resamples,
    producing stable shrinkage and conservative estimates of heterogeneity
    explained (R-squared-het). Methods described in Ahmad & Khan (2026).
